Hello! My name is Geoff Hom. I am one of the creators of Perfect Potty 
\f2 \uc0\u55357 \u57021 
\f0 . Here, I want to mention stuff beyond Perfect Potty's description.\
\
\
Perfect Potty has three main benefits:\
\
1) You can keep track of a child's potty attempts and whether they were successful 
\f2\fs40 \uc0\u55357 \u56489 
\f0\fs24  or not 
\f3\fs40 \cf3 \uc0\u10008 
\f0\fs24 \cf0 . You can then look at that history to look for patterns. For example, is the child more successful in the evening 
\f2 \uc0\u55356 \u57113 
\f0  than in the morning 
\f2\fs40 \uc0\u55356 \u57093 
\f0\fs24 ?\
\
Note: With the current version, you may now enter any character/symbol to denote a given potty attempt. This was in response to user requests to discern pee/poo/both, but also accidents vs successful attempts, etc. So, you can use any letter you like and come up with your own notation! Potties noted as successful will be \cf4 green\cf0 , and unsuccessful will be \cf3 red\cf0 . You may even use emoji, which are little pictures like the poo 
\f2\fs40 \uc0\u55357 \u56489 
